    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review Working Hours Sponsorship Rules for Domiciliary Care Providers & Workers",
        "additional_details": "We call for a review of the Home Office sponsorship rules for domiciliary care providers and sponsored workers, and for the following amendments to it:\r\n\u2022 Introduce a grace period allowing workers to retain their sponsorship when providers lose contracted hours.\r\n\u2022 Protect sponsored workers\u2019 visas when hours drop through no fault of the provider.\r\n\u2022 Provide clear, consistent sponsorship compliance guidance.\r\n\u2022 Introduce a transparent appeal or review process for licence suspensions or revocations.",
        "background": "Many domiciliary care providers rely on visa sponsored workers in their work to support vulnerable adults. We believe current Home Office rules unfairly punish normal hour changes, risking workers\u2019 visas, and that a review to ensure clear, fair rules is urgently needed.",
